# Purpose: Exclude unnecessary files from Docker build context.
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS:
#   - Reduces build context size (faster uploads to Docker daemon)
#   - Excludes sensitive files (secrets, credentials)
#   - Prevents build artifacts from contaminating image
#
# TEACHING VALUE:
#   - Shows students importance of build context optimization
#   - Demonstrates security best practices (exclude sensitive files)
#   - Explains .dockerignore vs. .gitignore differences
#
# AUDIENCE: Undergraduate / Graduate (DevOps basics)
